verses.text:
If I live up-on the high-way, This is what I'll do, I'll aid the wear-y trav-'lers, Who for-get through;
But if I dwell in the cit-y, Where the splen-dor's bright, I'll be a sun-beam al-ways, Shin-ing day and night;
If we are like Je-sus—Son of Right-eous-ness—Who set the bright ex-am-ple, Love-ly live to bless.
